CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 17, 1953, pg. 36, reads: "The JWJ's Open House - Last Sunday, Oct. 11, found Pittsburghers wending their way to the open house - house warming given by the John Wesley Johnsons in their new home at 3510 Iowa Street. Pittsburghers all were invited through Toki's column...  Center, Toki bids adieu to Mrs. Maude Dennis of Chicago, cousin of Mrs. Ira F. Lewis, shown left... - Teenie Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Harriet Lewis, Toki Schalk Johnson, and Maude Dennis standing in doorway of home of John Wesley Johnson, 3510 Iowa Street, Upper Hill District
